---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Version History">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Version History</h1>
      <p class="themed-text-muted">How RSM evolved through correction</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Current Version -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Current Version: v0.988</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">December 2025</p>

      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="themed-border border-b">
              <th class="pb-3 themed-text-muted">Change</th>
              <th class="pb-3 themed-text-muted">What It Does</th>
              <th class="pb-3 themed-text-muted">Why It Matters</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="themed-text-secondary">
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Postulate 4</td>
              <td>X * Y = k (Reciprocal Constraint)</td>
              <td>Makes P<sub>1</sub> = 1 derivation explicit and modular</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Part VI: Extensions</td>
              <td>Temporal O<sub>1</sub> derivation</td>
              <td>Shows present moment as parallel to spatial O<sub>1</sub></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="themed-border-light border-b">
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Appendix F</td>
              <td>Epistemic Status Classification</td>
              <td>Explicit tier system for all claims</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 font-semibold">Appendix G</td>
              <td>Dependency Graph</td>
              <td>Visual trace from foundations to claims</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- v0.987 -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">v0.987</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">December 2025</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Integration Round</p>
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>QED Compression:</strong> Added derivation summary after Abstract</li>
          <li><strong>Kleiber's Law:</strong> Second empirical domain (M^0.75 scaling)</li>
          <li><strong>Appendix C:</strong> Why pi must be irrational</li>
          <li><strong>Appendix D:</strong> Spring Coil visualization</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">Why: Prior version needed clearer empirical grounding and visualization aids.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- v0.986 -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">v0.986</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">December 2025</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Locked Corrections (Major)</p>
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>O<sub>1</sub> as generative:</strong> Changed from "empty center" to "generative position"</li>
          <li><strong>Infinite divisibility:</strong> Mathematical reason for unoccupiability made explicit</li>
          <li><strong>Measurement crisis:</strong> Static position incoherent, rotation necessary</li>
          <li><strong>Continuous transformation:</strong> No origin from void, no collapse into void</li>
          <li><strong>Euler's identity:</strong> Explicit Contrast/Rotation/Closure encoding</li>
          <li><strong>Three requirements:</strong> Formalized as core pattern</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">Why: v0.985 had conceptual drift. O<sub>1</sub> was being described with "emptiness" language that confused the framework's core claim.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- v0.985 -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">v0.985</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">December 2025</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Formalization Round</p>
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Russell's paradox:</strong> Analogy for V<sub>0</sub> prohibition</li>
          <li><strong>IVT formalization:</strong> O<sub>1</sub> existence proof structure</li>
          <li><strong>Minimax framing:</strong> phi selection principle</li>
          <li><strong>n=4 downgraded:</strong> From "prohibited" to "conjecture"</li>
          <li><strong>Eight-point synthesis:</strong> Summary structure</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">Why: Needed more rigorous mathematical grounding and explicit uncertainty.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- v0.984 -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">v0.984</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">December 2025</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Metasemantic Frame</p>
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>O<sub>1</sub> as forbidden fixed point:</strong> Precision on what "unoccupiable" means</li>
          <li><strong>Scoped phi derivation:</strong> Conditions made explicit</li>
          <li><strong>DDJ correspondence principle:</strong> Mapping rules formalized</li>
          <li><strong>Dependency graph:</strong> First version</li>
          <li><strong>Pedagogical principle:</strong> Presentation vs. ontology distinguished</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">Why: Framework was conflating derivation order with ontological priority.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- v0.983 -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">v0.983</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">December 2025</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">DDJ Deepening</p>
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Chapter 11:</strong> Semi-permeable membrane analysis (wheel/pot/room)</li>
          <li><strong>Chapter 25:</strong> zi/ming distinction formalized</li>
          <li><strong>Pedagogical vs. ontological:</strong> Sequence isn't priority</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">Why: DDJ readings were too shallow; needed structural analysis.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- v0.982 -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">v0.982</h2>
      <p class="themed-text-muted mb-4">December 2025</p>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Structure Overhaul</p>
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Core logic first:</strong> Reorganized presentation</li>
          <li><strong>phi derivation:</strong> Hurwitz theorem application</li>
          <li><strong>Verification tables:</strong> Systematic claim checking</li>
          <li><strong>Epistemic status:</strong> First classification attempt</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">Why: Document was becoming hard to navigate; needed clearer structure.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Earlier Versions -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Earlier Versions (v0.978-v0.981)</h2>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li><strong>v0.981:</strong> Refinements - 非 hedging, biology scope, 和/玄 distinction, 復 operator</li>
          <li><strong>v0.980:</strong> 玄牝 (generative void), 非 structure, developmental biology validation</li>
          <li><strong>v0.979:</strong> Derivation of phi from frame-invariance, master identity, pentagon connection</li>
          <li><strong>v0.978:</strong> Core operator grammar, Euler identity reading, 利/用 complementarity</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">These versions established the basic framework. Later versions corrected and refined.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Pre-v0.978 -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Pre-v0.978</h2>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="themed-text-secondary">
          Earlier work existed but wasn't versioned systematically. The v0.978+ series represents the formalized framework.
        </p>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-2 italic">
          Key insight: Version numbering started when we realized we needed to track corrections, not just additions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How to Read Old Documents -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How to Read Old Documents</h2>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="themed-text-secondary mb-4">
          If you encounter an earlier version:
        </p>
        <ol class="themed-text-secondary list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Check the version number.</strong> Pre-v0.986 documents may use "empty center" language.</li>
          <li><strong>Note the date.</strong> Earlier documents may lack locked corrections.</li>
          <li><strong>Prefer current version.</strong> Later versions correct earlier errors.</li>
          <li><strong>Core claims are stable.</strong> V<sub>0</sub> prohibition, O<sub>1</sub> existence, and three requirements haven't changed - only their articulation has improved.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Correction Principle -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Correction Principle</h2>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 pl-4 themed-text-secondary italic mb-4" style="border-color: var(--color-accent);">
          "Version history is evidence of honesty. A framework that never corrects itself either got everything right the first time (unlikely) or isn't paying attention to its mistakes."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="themed-text-secondary">
          RSM improves through explicit correction. Each version notes what changed and why. This is deliberate: we want mistakes to be visible and their fixes traceable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Upcoming -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Upcoming</h2>
      <div class="themed-surface border rounded-lg p-6">
        <p class="themed-text-secondary mb-2">
          Planned for future versions:
        </p>
        <ul class="themed-text-secondary space-y-1">
          <li>- Expanded empirical validation section</li>
          <li>- Additional DDJ chapter analyses</li>
          <li>- Cross-domain mapping refinements</li>
          <li>- Whatever corrections emerge from ongoing steelman analysis</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="themed-text-muted mt-4 italic">
          No roadmap is fixed. The framework develops in response to critique.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="text-center themed-text-muted text-sm themed-border border-t pt-8">
      <p class="italic mb-2">Correction is not weakness. Correction is honesty in action.</p>
      <p class="mb-4"><a href="/docset/rsm_complete.html" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Read RSM v0.988</a> | <a href="/claims" style="color: var(--color-accent);">What RSM Claims</a></p>
      <p>Will Goldstein & Claude - December 2025</p>
    </footer>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
